<br>
I have just discovered the joys of Karnor's Castle, and I am spending a lot of time there, just got two levels there this weekend. Down in the Upper Basement, I was grouped with some great people, talented players who could work really well as a team. We lost our cleric, fantastic one from Lotus Cult (sorry dear, forgot your name <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   ) to LD. We wait about 45 mins, a druid and I taking over heals, while we hoped for her to make it back. Giving up we OOC for a cleric.<br>
<br>
Enter Rezumall...<br>
<br>
Rez seemed like a nice enough guy, didn't talk much, but threw out the occasional CH while we pulled and killed everything we could. We had gotten a nice drop from a jailer earlier, so thought it might be fun to see what another had. Problem was, there were two. In comes the druid with Harmony. Before the harmony gets off, the monk waiting to pull twitches and aggros them both. Did I mention we have no enchanter? Hehe. Before I can ghetto mezz anything, the monk is down, the druid is down, and the rogue and pally are fighting. <br>
<br>
At this point, we are doing what any good group would do, and tell the cleric to camp. Nothing aggros in the room, and he can come back and rezz us all in exchange for being toys for them to kill time with while he makes a get away for the greater good (no messy CR).<br>
<br>
He won't camp, he runs into the hallway, casts a heal on someone, stands there. We keep telling this guy to camp, he won't camp, says nothing, just watches. Rogue is down, pally used his LoH. The cleric runs, taking one jailer with him, the pally follows him. I have one with me, and I don't know which way to turn to get out, and I KNOW the worst thing to do is die wandering around looking for the zone, best to stay in camp if you are lost (SolB Flashbacks). <br>
<br>
I see that the pally zoned, and the cleric not too far behind him. I managed to root the jailer, slow him and heal myself, and figured I would try to camp out while it was rooted, see if I can be of any help later. Better alive than dead I thought. Couldn't camp to 5 before roots broke on three occasions, so I continued to root, heal, and camp to get out of immediate danger. /q didn't appeal because I can't help myself while it beats the crap outta me while LD. I finally camp, log on an alt, tell everyone I am ok, then log back in to my Shaman.<br>
<br>
After all is said and done, we have lost 3, I camped, pally zoned, and cleric isn't saying a word, but apparently ended up in Sebilis. He hadn't zoned, he GATED to Sebilis after dropping his train on a CY group, then camped almost immediately, not responding to tells from the druid. By this time, the shouts are going across the zone, &quot;thanks for the train&quot;, and someone had died. I asked if a jailer was in there, and someone said one. So I apologized ooc for our poor choice of cleric, and set about to make a plan. <br>
<br>
First I checked out clerics, and Asion, level 60 was in Dreadlands, and graciously came in to help us with our rezzes. I was still stuck, not knowing which way to drag corpses. Kildayen, who's group was a victim of the cleric's train, was so great to come and drag the corpses. How he did three at the same time, I will never know. Is there a skill AoE summon corpse? hehe. I lost track of him up in the tower area, but I had cast levitate before I ran up and hopped over the wall, training my own passel of baddies to zone (TO THE LEFT). At least I don't train like a newbie hehe.<br>
<br>
Anyway, I wanted to tell the story in its entirety, leaving nothing out, for this is the absolute truth, and everyone should beware. We put absolute trust in our clerics, that if they can't keep us alive, at least they can rezz us, and this guy did neither. Better to have no cleric than to trust one who WILL fail you.<br>
<br>
This guy reminds me of a chanter I knew in my 20's name Mezumall, didn't even have Mezz memmed at Split Paw spires in SK...coincidence? /shrug we will never know...<br>
<br>
In closing this long assed post, I want to again thank the selfless assistance we received from Kildayen and Asion. They made a nasty situation a positive exp, and even though KC has a lot of squabbling, we all usually pull together to help out when the crap hits the fan. Thanks guys for making this game way funner than house work and doing laundry  <p><BR>
Whytspirit of the Nexus <BR>Wife to Hallace Nexusmaximus<BR>
