<hr size=1> First of all.. all clerics who keep GATE memmed during pulls should be taken out back and summarily shot. There's NO reason to waste a slot with that cheesedick spell when you could put something useful in it's spot. Clerics who run/gate/panic at the first sight of serious trouble should be taken back to Oasis to learn how to manage and deal with aggro. Learning what to do and keeping your cool during a nasty, nasty moment will not only earn you points with others but will make you more confident in your role. <br>
<br>
Second of all... Salta's a great guy. I have only grouped with him a couple of times but I met him on the boards and have had several interactions with him. Kudos to those like him who play honorably and have fun at the same time!! /salute<br>
<br>
Thirdly.. Anyone who says &quot;my B/F or G/F was playing my character&quot; as an excuse for severe and sudden lameness in the game is still liable for that person's actions. You can delegate authority but not responsibility. Excuses are excuses but pissing off a ton of people because someone's using your account is NOT an alibi. Making a mistake is fine.. we all do that. But not taking responsibility for your own actions - or lack thereof - is just a crappy thing to do. &quot;No scooby snacks for you!!&quot;<br>
<br>
Opal... Divine Aura is actually a VERY beneficial spell and will save your group TONS of mana over the long haul. Instead of having your secondary healers trying to save *you* after a heal-aggro beating (thereby dumping their own mana and gaining aggro onto themselves), go INVULN and let the critters float back to the melee folks high on the Aggro list OR wait for a MEZ to stick. But if it suits you better to not use, then by all means do what you do and keep on keepin' on, girl!! <br>
<br>
To All Clerics - when your group is taking it hard and heavy and it looks like it's the end for the lot of you, do what I do and look for a nearby gnome...<br>
<br>
... and just strap him on your chest to absorb the mobs hits. <br>
<br>
Gnomemore pain!! Yay!!!<br>
