<br>
1) I don't feel the loss of the spell slot. With six slots and DA I have more than enough to heal in a variety of situations and do the crowd control (roots/stuns) expected of me. If a situation requires a chain-stun, for example, dropping Complete Healing for the extra stun is a no-brainer (I won't be chain stunning AND casting ten second long heals, will I?)<br>
<br>
2) &quot;You can always DA and run.&quot; Ignoring places where DA just won't get you to the zone, or where running to a zone is otherwise not an option, you also train every poor schlep in your path. Shouting a warning doesn't help the person zoning in as you go out, either. You have a spell that avoids doing this, and you DON'T use it?<br>
<br>
3) The best argument I've seen against having Gate up says that you can always DA, then mem Gate while DA is up. That doesn't mesh well with my play style - I use DA like Jolt, to get aggro where it belongs, and almost always end up clicking it off to throw a heal. Being forced into memming Gate if I have to DA (if you don't, you KNOW what'll happen later) takes the one thing away from me that I trust the most after 60 levels - my judgement. I also feel uneasy about going for Gate after firing DA if the call to run is given because there's a good chance I'll be left alone when the evac goes off/when I stand up to Gate. And that means whatever made us run will be focussed on me.<br>
<br>
4) Why would I want to get away, instead of fighting to the bitter end? I trust my judgement as to when a fight is lost and when it's OK. I've fought until everything was dead, with me and two remaining tanks all at 40% health, and not Gated. I knew the fight would be won with the people in our group if we kept our heads, and it was. I've also seen a group I was in at D2 get three Krups out of nowhere, had them beeline the ENCH, and kill her before she could even cast a stun. Me, a monk, three rogues, and four Krups with respawn incoming, and the one rogue screaming &quot;RUN!&quot; I hit Gate, got out, and was able to organize the CR after the monk and one rogue abandoned us. My judgement told me that with the damage output we had, we couldn't kill four Krups before their damage output overwhelmed my ability to put people back together again. That leads to....<br>
<br>
5) CR. If camping in place isn't an option, then the group needs to fight back in. They're going to be a LOT better off with a cleric with full WIS/MANA and full buffs than with a cleric with 500ish AC, base HPs, 123 WIS, and no Symbols or buffs including symbol (Aegolism). Losing Symbol hurts, and no, a group facing CR does NOT rely on others being around to help out.<br>
<br>
So my Gate spell is staying right where it is, thank you. :-) I DO always bind by the zone I'm adventuring in or as close as possible to that, though. It's my job!<br>
<br>
Delores<br>
